The paper focuses on developing a driving model using machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions improvements in learning procedures and the use of numerical map data, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the behavior of autonomous vehicles on the road, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY).
